Step 1: Calculate the average total assets.
• Beginning Total Assets = 13,000,000.00 
• Ending Total Assets = 14,089,860.66 
• Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 14,089,860.66) / 2 = 27,089,860.66 / 2 = 13,544,930.33

Step 2: Find the Total Revenue.
• From the income statement, Total Revenue = 7,825,951.24

Step 3: Compute the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets 
• Ratio = 7,825,951.24 / 13,544,930.33 ≈ 0.578, which rounds to 0.58

Thus, the final answer is:

{"solution": {"Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.58"}}
